        "summary": "Code Review for Backend - Sample task",
        "description": "Pull Request Link:\nhttps://github.com/example-org/example-repo/pull/123\n\n **Review Checklist:** \n\n1. Code Quality:\n\n* [x] Code follows the established coding conventions and style guidelines.\n* [x] Meaningful variable and function names have been used.\n* [ ] Avoided unnecessary or redundant code.\n\n2. Functionality:\n\n* [ ] Implemented feature/task functions as described in the requirements.\n* [ ] Edge cases and error scenarios have been handled appropriately.\n\n3. Performance:\n\n* [ ] Code optimizations have been considered where necessary.\n* [ ] Avoided unnecessary database or API calls.\n\n4. Testing:\n\n* [ ] Unit tests have been written and cover critical functionality.\n* [ ] Integration tests cover interactions with other components if applicable.\n* [ ] All existing tests are passing.\n\n5. Documentation:\n\n* [ ] Updated relevant documentation, including API endpoints, if applicable.\n* [ ] Added inline comments where necessary for better code understanding.\n\n6. Security:\n\n* [ ] Sanitized inputs and avoided SQL injection vulnerabilities.\n* [ ] Ensured that sensitive data is handled securely, following our security guidelines.\n\n7. Review Comments:\n\n* [ ] Reviewed and addressed comments/suggestions made by reviewers.",
